snippet.textDisplay:
yeah, whatever.

this whole trilogy is terrible. the whole idea of starkiller base in the first movie was just laughably stupid. I mean come on, the deathstar was already this massive feat and now they have a base the size of a planet that's at least 20x larger than the deathstar?? even for star wars, that was pretty over the top and unbelievable.

first order loses their massive planet sized base that they dumped a ton of resources into and they're seemingly unaffected by it in the second movie. there's not even a mention of it. luke skywalker, the guy who turned darth vader from the dark side has become a whiny crybaby that has given up on the jedi. seriously? I can't believe that's the route rian Johnson went with luke. did anyone actually want to see luke act like that? is it even believable that luke could fall so far?

they brought back luke, han, and leia. this was our last chance at ever seeing these characters on screen together again portrayed by the original actors, and they couldn't even do that. they didn't share one scene together. not one single scene. seems like an absolute waste. now palpatine is magically back in the new movie. it's just a disaster. honestly, it's just stupid. this trilogy is an absolute mess. it makes star wars episodes 1-3 look like a masterpiece. five years ago if someone told me this is what the new trilogy was going to be like, I wouldn't believe them because it's so horribly crazy and awful.

i've never seen a franchise handled so poorly. you literally have to go out of your way to mishandle a franchise like this. i feel like a 12 year old could have came up with a better and more believable story than disney did

snippet.textDisplay:
Yo question, for people saying "don't follow his opinion" so why are you watching this? Because you're also using what he's said (plus I presume others) to decide on whether to watch this movie. I know I am. Why should people (and myself) spend money to watch something that other opinions have reliably informed me (and other people) as well as the confirmation of a majority of leaks, will not like? Especially something as divisive (I can't believe I'm saying this about star wars) as this?


Last I checked I'm not into 2 hours plus of visual discomfort. Vote with your money on this. You like it? Fine, watch it 30 times if you want, but others won't watch it even once. Just like I won't read every book that's "supposed" to be good I won't watch every movie just be because it's "supposed" to be good. Either case, I thank John for his opinion, I will now go gather more info and opinions now.
